10. Be2 b5 11. Bf3 Bb7 12. Rhe1 O-O 13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. exd5 Nf6 (14... Rfe8 15.
Rxe7 Rxe7 16. Bxe7 Nc5 17. Qe3 Re8 18. Bxd6 $1 $18) (14... Nc5 15. Qe2 $1) 15.
f5 Rfe8 16. fxg6 hxg6 17. Ne6 $1 $18) (6... b5 7. a4 $1 b4 8. Nd5 $1 e6 9.
Nxf6+ Qxf6 10. Be3 Bb7 11. Qc4 $1 {is awkward to meet.} (11. O-O-O Nd7 12. Nb3
$5)) (6... Nc6 7. Bg5 e6 8. O-O-O Bd7 9. f4 {is transposing to a tricky line
from the Rauzer Sicilian, 6 Bg5 e6 7 Qd3. But the Rauzer is quite different
