b5 8. b4 $5 {is again an interesting option if you like to shift your
attention to the queenside.} d5 (8... Bb7 9. a4 bxa4 10. Rxa4 Be7 11. O-O O-O
12. Rd1 (12. Nb3)) 9. exd5 Bxb4 10. O-O exd5 11. a4 $1 (11. Ncxb5 $5)) 7... b6
(7... Nc6 $5 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Be2 (9. Qg3 $5 d5 10. Be2 $1) 9... Be7 10. Qg3 O-O
11. O-O d5 12. e5 $1 $36) 8. Qg3 $1 {In the Sicilian, the frontal attack is
